parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can lead to accidents, especially if it occurs while driving at high speeds, and can cause inconvenience and distress to the driver.
symptoms: the vehicle stalls while driving on the highway

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the crankshaft pulley/harmonic balancer can cause loss of power steering, loss of brakes, and engine damage, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: thick black rubber ring separating from the pulley.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the air mass sensor can cause the engine to stall, leading to accidents or inconvenience, and can also cause further damage to the engine if not replaced.
symptoms: air mass sensor needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Oil leaks can cause engine damage, lead to fires, and cause accidents.
symptoms: oil leak from a pipe under the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected deployment of airbags can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities. It can also lead to a loss of control of the vehicle, which can result in crashes or near-misses.
symptoms: Airbags deploy without warning or impact
and potentially injuring the driver or passengers.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Airbags to Deploy in a Crash
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in a crash can increase the risk of injury or fatality to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a collision
despite the severity of the impact
and the driver or passengers may suffer injuries or fatalities as a result.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning seatbelt can increase the risk of injury or fatality to the driver or passengers in a crash.
symptoms: The seatbelt fails to restrain the driver or passenger

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front driveshaft can cause the airbag sensor to malfunction, leading to the erroneous deployment of airbags, which can result in injuries and accidents.
symptoms: causing the airbag sensor to malfunction
and the airbags to deploy unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, become stuck in gear, or refuse to shift, which can lead to accidents, especially on high-speed roads.
symptoms: causing the vehicle to become stuck in gear or unable to accelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the airbag sensor can cause the airbags to deploy unexpectedly, which can result in injuries and accidents.
symptoms: even in the absence of a crash or collision.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the window regulator can cause the windows to malfunction, which can be a nuisance and potentially lead to safety issues.
symptoms: failing to roll up or down properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front coil spring mount can cause the front suspension to collapse, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The front of the vehicle drops to the ground
the vehicle makes grinding and vibration noises
the spring perch is heavily corroded
the spring is noticeably bent and touching the struts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front wheel bearing can cause damage to the hub and spindle, brakes, and other surrounding components, leading to loss of vehicle control and accidents.
symptoms: causing damage to the hub and spindle
